&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7shifts is a scheduling and payroll platform designed to help restaurant teams thrive. With an easy-to-use app and industry-specific solutions, 7shifts saves time, reduces errors, and helps keep costs in check for over 55,000 restaurants. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mission is to simplify team management and improve performance for restaurants, with a long-term vision of &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;creating a thriving restaurant industry through the power of connected &amp;amp; engaged teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;Senior Financial Analyst &lt;/strong&gt;(FP&amp;amp;A) at 7shifts, you&#39;ll own the operating expense side of the business. Reporting to the Manager, FP&amp;amp;A, you&#39;ll be a key member of our lean, two-person FP&amp;amp;A team, leading expense forecasting, building driver-based financial models, and translating data into insights that guide decisions across the business. Your work will have immediate visibility and impact from day one. This is a highly collaborative business partnering role. You&#39;ll work closely with department leaders and executives to challenge assumptions, identify risks and opportunities, and tell the story behind the numbers. You&#39;ll also play a key role in migrating our financial models from spreadsheets to Drivetrain, helping modernize our planning process. With meaningful exposure to strategic initiatives, balance sheet and cash flow forecasting, this role offers strong opportunities for growth and development.&lt;/p&gt;
